Bash or roughly chop the @hazelnuts{10%g}.

Place a #pot over medium heat (no oil). Once hot, dry-fry the hazelnuts until toasted, shifting regularly, ~{2-3%mins}. Remove from the #pot and set aside.

Quarter and core the @apple{1} (quartered and cored). Thinly slice lengthways.

Halve the @orange{1}. Juice one-half then peel the rest with a #knife and remove the segments.

Chop the @Greek style cheese{100%g} into 1cm cubes.

Add @oil{1%tbsp}, 1 tbsp orange juice, half the @mustard{1/2%sachet} and @maple syrup{15%g} to a #salad bowl.

Mix well to make your dressing. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Just before serving, add the @salad leaves{40%g}, diced cheese, orange segments, half the toasted hazelnuts and apple slices to the #salad bowl.

Toss to coat everything in the dressing.

Divide the salad between plates.

Roll up the @sliced Irish ham{80%g} slices and arrange on top.

Sprinkle with the remaining hazelnuts.